id: pm-js02
title: Package lifecycle typo recovery should suggest action subcommands
description: "When users run mistyped package/extension lifecycle actions such as pm package descirbe --json or pm package catalogx --json, the lifecycle parser treats the token as a target and emits a generic missing-action error whose recovery suggests --install \"<value>\". Agents should get typo-aware suggestions for valid action subcommands such as describe or catalog instead. Duplicate check 2026-06-25: pm search --status all for package extension lifecycle typo recovery descirbe catalogx target install suggestions found related package/extension work but no exact item."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli",dx,recovery
created_at: "2026-06-25T00:06:32.677Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-25T00:42:18.617Z"
author: codex-audit-20260625
parent: pm-mpbb
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T00:12:20.747Z",codex-audit-20260625,"Evidence: compiled CLI now returns unknown_lifecycle_action for package descirbe/catalogx with suggested_retry pm package describe/catalog. Focused test passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts (110 tests)."
  "2026-06-25T00:42:17.795Z",codex-audit-20260625,"Evidence update: strict coverage initially caught new recovery branches; tests now cover exact action fallback, short typos, nearest later candidate ranking, and structured package recovery. Full release gate later passed literal 100/100/100/100 coverage."
